description:
This repository contains the code for simulating and analyzing turbulent brain dynamics in patients with traumatic brain injury (TBI)
using a whole-brain model based on coupled Hopf oscillators.
The model integrates empirical data—such as structural connectivity and resting-state fMRI—to capture altered dynamical regimes in lesioned brains
through a simulated attack approach.

The repository is organized into six folders:
(1) model-free – whole-brain turbulent-like dynamics;
(2) model-based – Hopf whole-brain model with intact structural connectivity;
(3) model-based-lesions – Hopf model after simulated attacks;
(4) CONN_preprocessing – CONN toolbox denoising outputs;
(5) time-series – inputs for model-free/model-based analyses;
(6) lesion-masks – code for the simulated attack approach.

For detailed methodology and usage instructions, please see the full README file:
[README.md](https://github.com/decolab/martinezmolina_TBI_turbu_les_Hopf/blob/main/README.md) (https://github.com/decolab/martinezmolina_TBI_turbu_les_Hopf/blob/main/README.md)
